{{lowercase title}} {{use dmy dates|date=March 2012}} {{Infobox Organization |name = bbodance |image_border = |logo = |size = |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = bbodance |motto = |formation = 1930 |extinction = |type = Dance Awarding Body |status = |purpose = |location = |region_served = |membership = |language = |leader_title = Executive Chairman |leader_name = Nicholas Espinosa |main_organ = Board of Directors |parent_organization = |affiliations = Council for Dance Education and Training |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = http://bbo.dance |remarks = }}
'''bbodance''', formerly the '''British Ballet Organization''' ('''BBO'''), is a dance [[examination board]] based in London, England.
== Overview == Formerly known as the British Ballet Organization, bbodance<ref>{{cite web|last=Wilson |first=Jessica |url=http://blog.dancedirect.com/2016/05/31/new-bbodance/ |title=The new bbodance - Dance Direct Blog |publisher=Blog.dancedirect.com |date=2016-05-31 |accessdate=2017-02-15}}</ref> was founded in England in 1930 by [[Edouard Espinosa]] and [[Eve Louise Kelland]], both noted dance teachers. It was established as a dance teaching society and developed a syllabus of Classical Ballet training. The BBO is now one of the leading dance examination boards in the United Kingdom and provides an examination syllabus in [[classical ballet]], [[Tap dance|tap]], [[Jazz dance|jazz]] and [[modern dance]], with a teacher training programme that qualifies people to work as dance teachers in the private and state sectors. The BBO is a registered dance awarding body of the Council for Dance Education and Training<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdet.org.uk/professional.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-08-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20050206063644/http://www.cdet.org.uk/professional.php |archivedate=6 February 2005 |df=dmy }}</ref> and its qualifications are accredited by the [[Qualifications and Curriculum Authority]] in England, the [[Department for Children, Education, Lifelong Learning and Skills]] (DCELLS) in Wales, and the [[Council for the Curriculum, Examinations and Assessment]] (CCEA) in Northern Ireland.<ref>http://www.ofqual.gov.uk/files/BBO_Final_PAM_Report.pdf{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> [[Michael Nunn]] and [[William Trevitt (dancer)|William Trevitt]], [[BalletBoyz]] founders, became new artistic directors of the British Ballet Organization, at the time when the company went through a major rebrand in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hemley |first=Matthew |url=https://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2016/michael-nunn-and-william-trevitt-to-modernise-rebranded-british-ballet-organisation/ |title=Michael Nunn and William Trevitt to modernise rebranded BBO |publisher=Thestage.co.uk |date=2016-05-09 |accessdate=2017-02-15}}</ref>
==References== {{Reflist}}
==External links== *{{official website|http://www.bbo.org.uk}}
